content.text:
Yes. Decisions have a `superseded_by` relation edge:

```sql
-- schema/surreal-schema.surql:497-499
DEFINE TABLE superseded_by TYPE RELATION IN decision OUT decision SCHEMAFULL;
DEFINE FIELD reason ON superseded_by TYPE option<string>;
DEFINE FIELD superseded_at ON superseded_by TYPE datetime;
```

So it's `decision:a ->superseded_by-> decision:b`, with optional `reason` and `superseded_at` fields. The decision status enum also includes `"superseded"` as a valid state.
